WEBVTT

1
00:00:05.000 --> 00:00:09.680
[blues song playing]

2
00:00:11.000 --> 00:00:17.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

3
00:00:22.000 --> 00:00:23.720
<i>♪ I put a spell on you ♪</i>

4
00:00:29.320 --> 00:00:30.840
<i>♪ 'Cause you're mine... ♪</i>

5
00:00:31.440 --> 00:00:32.760
{\an8}PILLS MIGRENO-NERVOSIN KOGUTEK
FLU. COLD. HEADACHES. TOOTHACHES

6
00:00:32.840 --> 00:00:35.040
{\an8}[Helena] <i>What kind of person
are you looking for?</i>

7
00:00:35.680 --> 00:00:39.360
A rich wife with a hundred grand.
In return I've got lots of tripe.

8
00:00:39.440 --> 00:00:40.480
Who could resist that?

9
00:00:40.560 --> 00:00:44.160
Someone who is put together.
highbrow. and well-mannered.

10
00:00:44.240 --> 00:00:46.720
I'm just not sure
how to phrase it so that...

11
00:00:48.480 --> 00:00:50.280
So. only men respond to it.

12
00:00:50.360 --> 00:00:51.200
[typing]

13
00:00:51.320 --> 00:00:53.320
[Helena] Beautiful woman seeks husband.

14
00:00:53.400 --> 00:00:58.280
What she lacks in money. she makes up
for in elegance and femininity.

15
00:01:00.200 --> 00:01:03.000
I don't mind an ugly broad.
so she don't cheat.

16
00:01:03.080 --> 00:01:07.120
[Helena] Applications along with a photo
should be sent.

17
00:01:07.200 --> 00:01:09.120
[typing continues]

18
00:01:10.440 --> 00:01:12.520
To "Miss pretty as a picture."

19
00:01:12.920 --> 00:01:13.760
Oh. well...

20
00:01:16.800 --> 00:01:18.280
To "The King of Hearts."

21
00:01:22.120 --> 00:01:24.320
All right. get these ready
for print. Mr. Cajmer.

22
00:01:24.440 --> 00:01:25.560
[Cajmer] Will do. ma'am.

23
00:01:26.200 --> 00:01:28.120
[instrumental music playing]

24
00:01:37.160 --> 00:01:40.520
FORTUNA AMANDI. classified ads

25
00:01:44.840 --> 00:01:46.200
[dog barks in distance]

26
00:01:47.080 --> 00:01:47.920
[Zuza crying]

27
00:01:53.520 --> 00:01:55.000
[intense music playing]

28
00:02:05.320 --> 00:02:06.160
[door closes]

29
00:02:07.000 --> 00:02:08.280
Which one?

30
00:02:08.360 --> 00:02:09.400
Her. Zuza.

31
00:02:13.320 --> 00:02:14.440
Go on. scram!

32
00:02:14.880 --> 00:02:15.920
[kisses]

33
00:02:16.400 --> 00:02:17.320
Let's go.

34
00:02:18.000 --> 00:02:19.920
Are you deaf? Outside.

35
00:02:21.320 --> 00:02:22.240
Come on.

36
00:02:29.680 --> 00:02:30.960
Bite down hard. kid.

37
00:02:33.200 --> 00:02:35.120
Grab the table and don't let go.

38
00:02:35.200 --> 00:02:36.840
[Zuza shuddering]

39
00:02:45.320 --> 00:02:46.560
You'll be all right.

40
00:02:47.400 --> 00:02:48.560
[groans in pain]

41
00:02:48.640 --> 00:02:50.160
[breathing heavily]

42
00:02:52.440 --> 00:02:53.640
[screaming in pain]

43
00:03:09.320 --> 00:03:14.080
WOMEN'S HELL

44
00:03:14.760 --> 00:03:15.840
[vehicles honking]

45
00:03:38.280 --> 00:03:40.040
[Helena] Are you here about an ad?

46
00:03:55.680 --> 00:03:58.400
[Ewa] Oh. another one?

47
00:04:09.120 --> 00:04:10.760
"About three months ago.

48
00:04:11.720 --> 00:04:14.720
I ran a personal ad
and a man replied to it.

49
00:04:14.800 --> 00:04:18.960
I only knew him by his pen name.
"Pure-hearted Jan."

50
00:04:20.600 --> 00:04:22.520
After corresponding. we arranged a date

51
00:04:22.600 --> 00:04:26.080
and at our first meeting.
I was then raped by him."

52
00:04:31.520 --> 00:04:33.760
[Ewa] "I confide
this horrible secret in you

53
00:04:33.840 --> 00:04:36.880
hoping you will ensure
that this man does not make

54
00:04:36.960 --> 00:04:40.080
further acquaintances with other women
through your magazine."

55
00:04:41.720 --> 00:04:43.080
There's no name. right?

56
00:04:44.160 --> 00:04:45.600
Just "Pure-hearted Jan."

57
00:04:47.800 --> 00:04:49.760
Look in our files for anyone by that name.

58
00:04:49.840 --> 00:04:50.680
[Ewa] Hmm.

59
00:04:53.520 --> 00:04:54.360
[door opens]

60
00:04:55.840 --> 00:04:57.360
[man] <i>Patient is 30 years old.</i>

61
00:04:58.640 --> 00:05:00.040
Multiple births.

62
00:05:00.760 --> 00:05:02.720
Which we can tell by?

63
00:05:03.720 --> 00:05:04.960
Mr. Heckmann.

64
00:05:05.760 --> 00:05:08.640
come. the vagina won't bite you. Come.

65
00:05:08.720 --> 00:05:09.720
[others laughing]

66
00:05:10.440 --> 00:05:14.440
[Emil] Uh. I see some scarring
from perineal tears.

67
00:05:15.680 --> 00:05:20.480
Uh... urethral damage from many births
is my assumption.

68
00:05:21.120 --> 00:05:22.400
Well. here.

69
00:05:24.120 --> 00:05:26.400
Now. let me see what we've got here.

70
00:05:29.560 --> 00:05:30.600
Uh...

71
00:05:33.520 --> 00:05:34.600
No. Mr. Heckmann.

72
00:05:35.520 --> 00:05:37.440
Palpation. please. if you would.

73
00:05:38.560 --> 00:05:39.960
[speaking indistinctly]

74
00:05:40.440 --> 00:05:41.960
[Emil] We have a closed cervix.

75
00:05:45.400 --> 00:05:47.360
Rather enlarged uterus.

76
00:05:47.440 --> 00:05:49.480
-She's pregnant.
-[Kasia] What?

77
00:05:49.640 --> 00:05:51.200
Past the first trimester.

78
00:05:51.280 --> 00:05:53.320
No. Doctor. I can't be.

79
00:05:53.760 --> 00:05:55.000
Good. Heckmann.

80
00:05:55.120 --> 00:05:56.440
Mr. Jedlicki.

81
00:05:56.520 --> 00:05:59.240
you're gonna walk us
through a natural delivery.

82
00:05:59.320 --> 00:06:00.640
You can get dressed. ma'am.

83
00:06:02.280 --> 00:06:05.040
-[men speaking indistinctly]
-Careful.

84
00:06:05.120 --> 00:06:06.600
[Kasia] Please. doctor.

85
00:06:07.800 --> 00:06:09.240
My husband lost his job.

86
00:06:09.320 --> 00:06:12.000
I have seven kids to feed.
and my youngest can't walk.

87
00:06:14.720 --> 00:06:17.600
If you don't help me. I might as well jump
in front of a train.

88
00:06:17.680 --> 00:06:19.840
I'm not a real doctor yet.

89
00:06:20.400 --> 00:06:21.920
I'll pay you.

90
00:06:22.040 --> 00:06:24.800
Miss. abortion is an illegal procedure.

91
00:06:25.640 --> 00:06:28.920
I'll speak with Dr. Łabęda.
Come tomorrow night. okay?

92
00:06:29.000 --> 00:06:31.800
-My shift begins at eight.
-[Dr. Łabęda] Mr. Heckmann!

93
00:06:31.880 --> 00:06:33.360
I'll try to convince him.

94
00:06:34.920 --> 00:06:36.480
[Dr. Łabęda] Face presentation. please.

95
00:06:37.000 --> 00:06:38.320
[men laughing]

96
00:06:41.600 --> 00:06:42.840
Doctor?

97
00:06:44.840 --> 00:06:46.080
What is it?

98
00:06:46.160 --> 00:06:47.880
You know this won't stop her.

99
00:06:48.200 --> 00:06:50.120
Some butcher will gladly do it.

100
00:06:50.200 --> 00:06:54.200
And he'll use some spoke for the job
and make her my problem.

101
00:06:54.880 --> 00:06:56.480
We always see them again.

102
00:06:56.680 --> 00:07:00.000
Poor woman.
Not even 30. but clearly unwell.

103
00:07:01.560 --> 00:07:04.400
-It'd be breaking the law.
-But I could help her.

104
00:07:06.520 --> 00:07:09.760
Every doctor has
his own personal graveyard.

105
00:07:09.840 --> 00:07:11.960
You'll learn that soon enough.

106
00:07:12.040 --> 00:07:15.200
If this patient were rich.
we wouldn't be hesitating. would we?

107
00:07:15.600 --> 00:07:16.760
Hmm.

108
00:07:17.280 --> 00:07:19.520
There are so many idealists in school.

109
00:07:19.600 --> 00:07:22.200
then they end up
and vanish after graduation.

110
00:07:26.320 --> 00:07:28.160
When did you last have a proper meal?

111
00:07:29.600 --> 00:07:31.040
How about you go home

112
00:07:31.120 --> 00:07:34.520
and take that pretty sister of yours
to Engler's for dinner?

113
00:07:34.600 --> 00:07:35.960
I've got a table there.

114
00:07:36.880 --> 00:07:39.000
Go have some fun. for once.

115
00:07:44.000 --> 00:07:46.480
Kochanowicz. you're finally gonna
settle down one day?

116
00:07:46.560 --> 00:07:47.760
Don't count on it. ma'am.

117
00:07:47.840 --> 00:07:51.680
But modern marriages don't have to mean
the end of fun and adventure anymore.

118
00:07:52.840 --> 00:07:55.760
Take Miss Krzywicka for one. And. Boy.

119
00:07:55.840 --> 00:07:59.320
Ewa. archive the correspondence please.

120
00:07:59.920 --> 00:08:01.080
Mr. Cajmer!

121
00:08:01.160 --> 00:08:03.240
Um... Yep. printing now.

122
00:08:04.800 --> 00:08:06.040
[telephone ringing]

123
00:08:06.120 --> 00:08:07.240
Ewa...

124
00:08:13.520 --> 00:08:15.760
Maks. I'm going to Herze's with Ewa.

125
00:08:16.000 --> 00:08:18.840
Oh. Mr. Boy-Żeleński.

126
00:08:20.400 --> 00:08:21.480
Good morning.

127
00:08:22.520 --> 00:08:23.680
Good morning.

128
00:08:24.160 --> 00:08:25.240
[kisses]

129
00:08:25.400 --> 00:08:27.400
A beautiful progressive woman
like yourself

130
00:08:27.480 --> 00:08:31.280
-must surely have views on women's rights.
-My wife is in charge of the ads.

131
00:08:31.360 --> 00:08:33.200
You write about women's rights.

132
00:08:33.720 --> 00:08:36.040
[Boy-Żeleński] Listen to this.

133
00:08:36.280 --> 00:08:39.720
A washerwoman from Mielec
killed her five month old.

134
00:08:39.800 --> 00:08:41.280
smothering it with soil.

135
00:08:41.600 --> 00:08:43.680
The court sentenced her to hang.

136
00:08:44.000 --> 00:08:45.440
She had 12 kids at home.

137
00:08:45.520 --> 00:08:47.520
That justifies murder?

138
00:08:47.600 --> 00:08:50.280
Well. it doesn't.
but I believe it makes us complicit

139
00:08:50.360 --> 00:08:52.080
if we don't fight for birth control.

140
00:08:52.160 --> 00:08:54.360
Men want to fight for contraception?

141
00:08:55.680 --> 00:08:58.400
Women should choose for themselves.
not the legal system.

142
00:08:58.480 --> 00:08:59.520
About what?

143
00:09:00.000 --> 00:09:02.880
It's better to kill a child
before or after birth?

144
00:09:02.960 --> 00:09:04.760
[Maks] Darling. you should go.

145
00:09:05.280 --> 00:09:06.760
Don't want to be late.

146
00:09:06.840 --> 00:09:09.800
It's a sensitive topic
and really not for us.

147
00:09:10.560 --> 00:09:12.160
We focus on marriage here.

148
00:09:14.680 --> 00:09:15.680
[door opens]

149
00:09:15.760 --> 00:09:20.480
As you see. it's a touchy subject
and stirs up people's emotions.

150
00:09:20.560 --> 00:09:23.440
Women do this to themselves.
if I could only make them aware--

151
00:09:23.520 --> 00:09:27.240
But strong emotions
are our bread and butter here.

152
00:09:27.320 --> 00:09:31.760
I mean. with your talents and mine.
we can stir up all the emotions we want.

153
00:09:32.760 --> 00:09:35.160
So. you're saying you'll run the article?

154
00:09:35.840 --> 00:09:38.000
If it's for progress. I'm on board.

155
00:09:38.440 --> 00:09:40.280
I knew you were a stand-up guy.

156
00:09:40.360 --> 00:09:41.240
Good.

157
00:09:43.240 --> 00:09:45.160
Did I mention I'm a writer. too?

158
00:09:45.960 --> 00:09:47.880
[instrumental music playing]

159
00:09:52.880 --> 00:09:54.760
[Helena] Stop it. Don't be so nervous.

160
00:09:54.840 --> 00:09:57.560
We do have "Pure-hearted Jan"
in the files.

161
00:09:57.640 --> 00:09:58.800
Oh. you checked?

162
00:09:59.520 --> 00:10:02.520
Looks like he's only replied
to just one ad so far.

163
00:10:03.440 --> 00:10:05.440
A man named. "Pure-hearted..."

164
00:10:06.240 --> 00:10:09.400
-It's clearly a fake name.
-It's the one he gave.

165
00:10:10.080 --> 00:10:15.640
The girl's name is Zuzanna Heckmann.
but... can we believe her story?

166
00:10:17.080 --> 00:10:19.640
It'd be best if Uncle Maks
handled it. don't you think?

167
00:10:19.720 --> 00:10:21.720
Don't worry about it right now.

168
00:10:21.800 --> 00:10:23.560
-She could just be a liar.
-[Helena] Ewa!

169
00:10:23.640 --> 00:10:25.400
Some guy dumped her. and now she wants

170
00:10:25.480 --> 00:10:27.920
-to destroy his and our reputation.
-[Helena] Please!

171
00:10:28.000 --> 00:10:31.080
-I mean. what if our clients find out?
-I'll handle them.

172
00:10:31.600 --> 00:10:33.840
Focus. Your big day's coming up.

173
00:10:33.920 --> 00:10:35.480
Look how pretty you are.

174
00:10:36.680 --> 00:10:38.960
[Ewa] I'll die of boredom with Ludwik.

175
00:10:39.040 --> 00:10:40.280
Just sitting at home.

176
00:10:41.160 --> 00:10:44.000
And would Bruno give you
the life that you want?

177
00:10:44.080 --> 00:10:45.320
[Ewa] How do you...

178
00:10:46.200 --> 00:10:47.520
[both chuckle]

179
00:10:48.960 --> 00:10:50.600
We're just friends. and...

180
00:10:50.680 --> 00:10:53.480
-Ah?
-He lends me books sometimes.

181
00:10:53.560 --> 00:10:54.560
Mm-hmm.

182
00:10:56.680 --> 00:10:58.320
Well. I hate to burst your bubble

183
00:10:59.680 --> 00:11:02.840
but those passionate. sensual moments
tend to fade over time.

184
00:11:03.920 --> 00:11:05.080
[both laugh]

185
00:11:10.080 --> 00:11:11.360
[breathing heavily]

186
00:11:11.600 --> 00:11:12.840
[thuds]

187
00:11:13.360 --> 00:11:14.480
[Ewa] Helena?

188
00:11:16.080 --> 00:11:18.360
Auntie? Helena?

189
00:11:19.400 --> 00:11:20.480
Someone help!

190
00:11:21.280 --> 00:11:22.680
[cycle whirring]

191
00:11:26.120 --> 00:11:27.760
[dogs bark in distance]

192
00:11:36.280 --> 00:11:37.720
[keys jingling]

193
00:11:38.040 --> 00:11:39.280
[door closes]

194
00:11:41.920 --> 00:11:42.960
She's so messy.

195
00:11:45.680 --> 00:11:46.720
Zuza?

196
00:11:48.480 --> 00:11:50.240
Your big brother is taking you out.

197
00:11:53.880 --> 00:11:55.120
Zuza. you sleeping?

198
00:11:56.040 --> 00:11:57.320
[train chugging]

199
00:12:02.160 --> 00:12:03.560
[intense music playing]

200
00:12:10.040 --> 00:12:11.440
[Emil sobbing]

201
00:12:31.080 --> 00:12:33.040
Zuza. Zuza. Zuza...

202
00:12:34.480 --> 00:12:35.800
[crying]

203
00:12:51.600 --> 00:12:53.080
[door creaking]

204
00:12:53.360 --> 00:12:56.040
[Maks] Darling. I'm home.

205
00:12:57.240 --> 00:13:00.160
Sorry I'm late.
I had to grab a drink with Boy.

206
00:13:00.240 --> 00:13:02.600
What a stand-up guy. We had a great time!

207
00:13:03.000 --> 00:13:04.040
[kissing]

208
00:13:07.040 --> 00:13:08.080
[Maks humming]

209
00:13:08.160 --> 00:13:10.400
Well. it sounds to me like you. sir.

210
00:13:10.480 --> 00:13:13.400
will have to start
leaving the office earlier.

211
00:13:13.480 --> 00:13:15.280
[Maks] It's such a perfect night out.

212
00:13:16.120 --> 00:13:17.840
I walked all the way here

213
00:13:17.920 --> 00:13:21.280
and had this little tune
dancing around in my head.

214
00:13:22.520 --> 00:13:24.280
[humming]

215
00:13:27.480 --> 00:13:28.840
[playing piano]

216
00:13:31.240 --> 00:13:32.720
[singing in Polish]

217
00:13:54.320 --> 00:13:55.720
[laughs]

218
00:13:56.360 --> 00:13:58.280
I have a little surprise for you. too.

219
00:13:58.560 --> 00:14:00.240
[chuckles] What kind of surprise?

220
00:14:03.720 --> 00:14:05.760
-For quite some time...
-For quite some time.

221
00:14:05.920 --> 00:14:07.600
you thought I was a genius!

222
00:14:07.960 --> 00:14:09.400
[laughs]

223
00:14:10.960 --> 00:14:14.480
Uh... For quite some time now.

224
00:14:15.560 --> 00:14:17.560
my head's been feeling all dizzy.

225
00:14:20.760 --> 00:14:22.720
And today I had a bout of nausea.

226
00:14:25.680 --> 00:14:28.600
I didn't want to say
anything earlier and jinx it.

227
00:14:30.160 --> 00:14:31.520
So. does that mean...

228
00:14:34.600 --> 00:14:35.640
Oh. sweetheart.

229
00:14:36.000 --> 00:14:37.000
[kissing]

230
00:14:38.080 --> 00:14:40.320
Oh! My son!

231
00:14:40.680 --> 00:14:42.440
-[kissing]
-[laughing]

232
00:14:43.800 --> 00:14:45.040
Your daddy loves you.

233
00:14:46.480 --> 00:14:47.600
And if it's a girl?

234
00:14:47.680 --> 00:14:51.760
And if it's a girl.
she'll be as beautiful as her mother.

235
00:14:52.640 --> 00:14:53.960
[laughing]

236
00:14:54.760 --> 00:14:56.200
[train chugging]

237
00:14:58.320 --> 00:14:59.880
[intense music playing]

238
00:15:04.560 --> 00:15:05.880
Mademoiselle Zizi.

239
00:15:07.680 --> 00:15:09.560
You knew the deceased. Superintendent?

240
00:15:11.880 --> 00:15:13.120
She was a dancer.

241
00:15:14.120 --> 00:15:15.680
Her legs were incredible.

242
00:15:17.120 --> 00:15:18.120
What a shame.

243
00:15:18.200 --> 00:15:21.120
[Emil] For a week. I've basically
been living at the clinic.

244
00:15:21.960 --> 00:15:23.160
I just came home.

245
00:15:30.960 --> 00:15:32.200
Emil Heckmann.

246
00:15:32.520 --> 00:15:33.600
She's my sister.

247
00:15:34.160 --> 00:15:37.960
Well. it would appear your sister
committed a serious crime. Mr. Heckmann.

248
00:15:38.760 --> 00:15:42.160
You practice at Dr. Łabęda's
gynecology clinic. don't you?

249
00:15:44.160 --> 00:15:47.160
If I had performed it.
she would still be here. sir.

250
00:15:48.080 --> 00:15:49.440
Please write that down.

251
00:15:50.120 --> 00:15:53.400
Add that this only happens
thanks to this backwards legal system.

252
00:15:53.480 --> 00:15:56.440
And both of you are complicit!
Take that statement.

253
00:16:03.760 --> 00:16:05.560
I didn't even know she was pregnant.

254
00:16:06.920 --> 00:16:10.640
Let me guess. You didn't know she danced
in burlesque shows as Zizi either.

255
00:16:11.800 --> 00:16:13.440
She was a ballet dancer.

256
00:16:14.040 --> 00:16:17.560
-She studied with Felicja Adamowicz.
-Sure. kid.

257
00:16:23.960 --> 00:16:25.240
The autopsy will be crucial.

258
00:16:25.320 --> 00:16:27.360
But I'm sure you're aware. Mr. Heckmann.

259
00:16:27.440 --> 00:16:28.600
I'll cooperate.

260
00:16:30.480 --> 00:16:32.200
Just don't go skipping town.

261
00:16:32.760 --> 00:16:34.000
[intense music playing]

262
00:16:50.280 --> 00:16:51.640
You may get dressed. ma'am.

263
00:16:53.320 --> 00:16:55.400
[Maks] Well. Doctor? Any good news for us?

264
00:16:58.960 --> 00:17:01.920
[Dr. Łabęda] I'm afraid
there's no pregnancy.

265
00:17:04.360 --> 00:17:05.480
I'm very sorry.

266
00:17:09.680 --> 00:17:11.280
Well. what about the dizzy spells?

267
00:17:11.360 --> 00:17:13.680
She told me she was faint and nauseous!

268
00:17:13.760 --> 00:17:16.040
A bad reaction to arsenic. that's all.

269
00:17:16.120 --> 00:17:19.160
I recommend you to discontinue it
and let's change the treatment.

270
00:17:19.240 --> 00:17:20.880
Or maybe change our doctor.

271
00:17:21.520 --> 00:17:24.920
Another year of your efforts.
and we still have nothing to show for it.

272
00:17:25.000 --> 00:17:28.440
Professor. I'm 34 years old.
We don't have time to waste.

273
00:17:29.440 --> 00:17:30.560
[Dr. Łabęda] Here.

274
00:17:32.360 --> 00:17:35.160
-Thank you.
-There is a new procedure...

275
00:17:37.320 --> 00:17:40.440
that I recommend for infertile women.

276
00:17:42.760 --> 00:17:46.240
Where we would implant a donor ovary
in the abdominal wall.

277
00:17:48.480 --> 00:17:51.440
A donor? I'm not sure I understand.

278
00:17:52.200 --> 00:17:55.440
Transplants from the deceased
are the future in medicine. ma'am.

279
00:17:56.200 --> 00:17:59.680
The method isn't fully proven yet.
but neither are many other breakthroughs.

280
00:17:59.760 --> 00:18:01.560
now widely used in medicine.

281
00:18:01.640 --> 00:18:03.960
Such as X-rays or insulin. for example.

282
00:18:07.840 --> 00:18:11.360
But you would be transplanting it
and putting it in my body?

283
00:18:11.440 --> 00:18:12.560
Oh. no. not me. No.

284
00:18:13.640 --> 00:18:16.800
But we can bring Dr. Voronoff from Paris.
and he would perform it.

285
00:18:17.520 --> 00:18:20.240
A brilliant specialist
and believer of this method.

286
00:18:21.080 --> 00:18:23.360
He's done hundreds of such procedures.

287
00:18:23.640 --> 00:18:25.440
-How soon?
-Maks.

288
00:18:26.120 --> 00:18:27.480
Darling. please.

289
00:18:28.320 --> 00:18:30.280
We'll discuss it at home
and get back to you.

290
00:18:32.960 --> 00:18:33.960
[door opens]

291
00:18:34.680 --> 00:18:36.160
[engine running]

292
00:18:40.440 --> 00:18:42.960
I don't want to argue.
I'll drive you home.

293
00:18:43.280 --> 00:18:45.440
I still have things to take care of.

294
00:18:45.520 --> 00:18:47.280
What could be more important?

295
00:18:51.040 --> 00:18:52.600
I'm so exhausted.

296
00:18:52.680 --> 00:18:55.720
I've been taking arsenic for months.
I'm so tired.

297
00:18:55.800 --> 00:18:57.400
I have to rest. Maks.

298
00:18:57.480 --> 00:19:01.000
-Then quit the editorial job.
-But I love my job.

299
00:19:02.520 --> 00:19:04.200
So. then. are you giving up?

300
00:19:10.320 --> 00:19:11.920
This procedure is risky.

301
00:19:12.000 --> 00:19:13.520
Do you really want this for us?

302
00:19:15.840 --> 00:19:16.960
I wanted children.

303
00:19:17.840 --> 00:19:18.880
With you.

304
00:19:20.520 --> 00:19:22.320
But if you're not sure anymore--

305
00:19:22.400 --> 00:19:23.400
-I am.
-Are you?

306
00:19:23.480 --> 00:19:24.920
[Helena] Mm-hmm.

307
00:19:25.000 --> 00:19:26.080
Then prove it.

308
00:19:33.400 --> 00:19:35.360
[paper boy shouting indistinctly]

309
00:19:39.240 --> 00:19:42.680
Fresh papers here.
hot off the Warsaw presses.

310
00:19:42.760 --> 00:19:43.880
Read it while it's hot.

311
00:19:43.960 --> 00:19:45.240
Fresh papers here.

312
00:19:46.440 --> 00:19:47.720
You got it. sir.

313
00:19:47.800 --> 00:19:48.720
Here you are.

314
00:20:10.440 --> 00:20:11.360
Emil Heckmann?

315
00:20:11.800 --> 00:20:13.240
What are you doing here?

316
00:20:13.320 --> 00:20:14.640
Can we talk somewhere?

317
00:20:18.640 --> 00:20:20.320
Is Zizi feeling any better?

318
00:20:20.840 --> 00:20:22.480
We all miss her at school.

319
00:20:22.920 --> 00:20:26.600
She's been absent six months
and no one's heard of you there.

320
00:20:26.680 --> 00:20:27.600
Just ask Zuza.

321
00:20:31.640 --> 00:20:32.800
Well. Zuza's dead.

322
00:20:44.240 --> 00:20:45.440
You're lying.

323
00:20:48.640 --> 00:20:50.280
Fela. what the hell did you do?

324
00:20:56.160 --> 00:20:58.080
[men in street shouting indistinctly]

325
00:21:13.960 --> 00:21:15.080
[Fela] Here.

326
00:21:17.280 --> 00:21:18.600
This was our dressing room.

327
00:21:21.200 --> 00:21:23.240
We danced together here for six months.

328
00:21:24.200 --> 00:21:25.280
[woman] Wow.

329
00:21:27.840 --> 00:21:29.400
Give him a little quickie. all right?

330
00:21:29.480 --> 00:21:30.800
Oh. get lost. Mańka.

331
00:21:31.200 --> 00:21:32.360
I said beat it!

332
00:21:33.320 --> 00:21:34.280
Be that way.

333
00:21:34.360 --> 00:21:35.520
[Fela] Get out.

334
00:21:44.960 --> 00:21:46.560
[intense music playing]

335
00:21:51.800 --> 00:21:52.640
NOTEBOOK
Zizi

336
00:21:55.160 --> 00:21:56.480
[Emil] You got her into this.

337
00:21:56.880 --> 00:21:59.240
-[Fela] She wanted this life.
-Oh. really?

338
00:21:59.320 --> 00:22:01.080
Why did she never tell me about it?

339
00:22:01.160 --> 00:22:03.240
Would you have let her perform if she did?

340
00:22:03.760 --> 00:22:06.080
She wanted to tell you once we made it.

341
00:22:06.160 --> 00:22:08.080
This shithole isn't where you make it.

342
00:22:08.160 --> 00:22:10.320
[woman whistles] Fela. move it. will you?

343
00:22:10.400 --> 00:22:11.480
[Fela] Jeez!

344
00:22:11.680 --> 00:22:13.560
Where did Ordonówna start?

345
00:22:14.000 --> 00:22:15.280
And Pola Negri?

346
00:22:15.360 --> 00:22:19.040
Zizi always dreamed of acting
and singing in the movies.

347
00:22:23.960 --> 00:22:25.200
Help me.

348
00:22:28.320 --> 00:22:29.640
[woman] Ah. okay.

349
00:22:29.960 --> 00:22:33.000
All right. are you guys ready?
It's almost show time!

350
00:22:33.760 --> 00:22:35.560
Any idea who the father was?

351
00:22:37.480 --> 00:22:40.000
She only told me
what she cared to tell me.

352
00:22:40.080 --> 00:22:42.640
Now get out of here or Lew will kill me.

353
00:22:43.680 --> 00:22:44.800
Lew?

354
00:22:48.200 --> 00:22:50.000
[jazz band playing]

355
00:22:58.400 --> 00:23:00.880
[Lew] Oh. look who decided
to wander in at this hour!

356
00:23:00.960 --> 00:23:03.320
-[Fela] I'm sorry.
-Apologies! Apologies!

357
00:23:04.600 --> 00:23:05.640
What's going on?

358
00:23:05.720 --> 00:23:07.200
Seriously.

359
00:23:10.120 --> 00:23:11.160
What do you want?

360
00:23:11.920 --> 00:23:13.240
You little shit!

361
00:23:16.640 --> 00:23:18.680
[moaning]

362
00:23:19.280 --> 00:23:20.760
Get the fuck out of here.

363
00:23:23.040 --> 00:23:25.320
Which one of you dragged that man in here?

364
00:23:26.640 --> 00:23:27.480
Huh?

365
00:23:44.480 --> 00:23:45.760
Turn that off.

366
00:23:49.600 --> 00:23:50.680
[music stops playing]

367
00:23:57.120 --> 00:23:59.040
Let me serve you something?

368
00:23:59.120 --> 00:24:01.080
Did my husband say when he'd be back?

369
00:24:01.920 --> 00:24:04.640
Uh. he just said not to wait for him.

370
00:24:06.560 --> 00:24:08.960
Tell him I said the same when he shows up.

371
00:24:12.840 --> 00:24:13.800
[door opens]

372
00:24:13.880 --> 00:24:15.920
[slow instrumental music playing]

373
00:24:25.960 --> 00:24:27.880
[metal clattering]

374
00:24:37.840 --> 00:24:39.520
[chittering]

375
00:24:39.600 --> 00:24:41.200
[door opens]

376
00:24:42.240 --> 00:24:43.720
[door shuts]

377
00:24:49.680 --> 00:24:51.440
Same as last time.

378
00:24:51.520 --> 00:24:54.840
Róża. even sugar
has gotten more expensive.

379
00:24:54.920 --> 00:24:56.200
[Róża sighs]

380
00:24:58.040 --> 00:25:00.320
You greedy little bastard.

381
00:25:03.760 --> 00:25:07.200
[sniffs] Mmm.
Some first class goods there.

382
00:25:13.520 --> 00:25:15.320
<i>[Daydream</i> by Wallace Collection playing]

383
00:25:15.400 --> 00:25:17.160
That's a good girl.

384
00:25:50.280 --> 00:25:51.800
-Password?
-Tenderness.

385
00:25:51.880 --> 00:25:53.480
Come in. ma'am.

386
00:25:53.560 --> 00:25:55.760
[laughter]

387
00:25:57.280 --> 00:25:59.480
[Róża] Helena!

388
00:25:59.560 --> 00:26:02.240
My darling. you haven't been here in ages.

389
00:26:02.320 --> 00:26:04.880
I heard the wonderful news.
Congratulations.

390
00:26:04.960 --> 00:26:06.400
False alarm. actually.

391
00:26:07.800 --> 00:26:08.920
[sighs]

392
00:26:10.720 --> 00:26:12.560
I want to dance.

393
00:26:12.640 --> 00:26:14.320
Why is there no one to dance with?

394
00:26:14.400 --> 00:26:16.360
Calm down. Sit and tell me everything.

395
00:26:16.440 --> 00:26:19.240
I don't want to.
I want to forget just for a moment.

396
00:26:19.320 --> 00:26:21.440
[laughs] Then lie down here.

397
00:26:22.560 --> 00:26:24.120
There you go. Come.

398
00:26:24.200 --> 00:26:25.480
You'll love this.

399
00:26:26.600 --> 00:26:27.720
Mmm.

400
00:26:29.480 --> 00:26:30.880
Opium.

401
00:26:31.880 --> 00:26:32.840
[sighs]

402
00:26:33.360 --> 00:26:34.640
[sighs]

403
00:26:35.800 --> 00:26:36.840
Yes.

404
00:26:36.920 --> 00:26:39.760
Your husband should see you
in this moment.

405
00:26:40.680 --> 00:26:45.400
How confident and beautiful you are. dear.

406
00:26:46.640 --> 00:26:48.160
Just let it in.

407
00:26:49.400 --> 00:26:50.880
[exhales]

408
00:26:50.960 --> 00:26:52.120
[Róża] Ready?

409
00:26:55.680 --> 00:26:57.800
Now open up and look.

410
00:26:57.880 --> 00:26:59.760
This will help you.

411
00:27:02.520 --> 00:27:03.960
[camera shutter clicking]

412
00:27:04.040 --> 00:27:05.760
[Róża] You are free.

413
00:27:06.800 --> 00:27:08.640
[Helena] Mmm.

414
00:27:08.720 --> 00:27:10.080
[Róża] Beautiful.

415
00:27:10.960 --> 00:27:12.400
[Helena] Mmm.

416
00:27:17.840 --> 00:27:19.320
[Helena exhales]

417
00:27:22.480 --> 00:27:25.760
Your husband needs you this juicy.

418
00:27:26.960 --> 00:27:28.720
[Helena] Mmm.

419
00:27:28.800 --> 00:27:30.720
[Róża] Go home and show him.

420
00:27:31.680 --> 00:27:34.080
Show him the goddess that you are.

421
00:27:35.000 --> 00:27:37.000
[Helena exhales]

422
00:27:37.840 --> 00:27:40.360
[classical music playing]

423
00:27:52.640 --> 00:27:53.560
[Helena exhales]

424
00:27:53.640 --> 00:27:55.680
-[camera shutter clicks]
-[exhales]

425
00:27:58.040 --> 00:28:00.120
-[camera shutter clicks]
-[exhales]

426
00:28:01.600 --> 00:28:03.080
[camera shutter clicks]

427
00:28:11.080 --> 00:28:13.080
[man panting]

428
00:28:15.760 --> 00:28:17.240
[panting]

429
00:28:23.000 --> 00:28:24.800
[grunting]

430
00:28:30.720 --> 00:28:32.440
-[exhales]
-[music stops playing]

431
00:28:32.520 --> 00:28:35.080
[upbeat music playing over speakers]

432
00:28:35.160 --> 00:28:40.000
[Róża laughing in distance]
Ludwik! [laughs]

433
00:28:40.080 --> 00:28:43.400
[speaking indistinctly. laughs]

434
00:28:44.120 --> 00:28:47.120
Maks! Maks! Come here. look at this.

435
00:28:47.200 --> 00:28:48.800
[Róża laughs]

436
00:28:49.920 --> 00:28:51.400
No.

437
00:28:51.480 --> 00:28:55.400
No. [laughs. speaks indistinctly]

438
00:28:58.560 --> 00:29:01.240
[Maks] Are you really switching
from tires to condoms?

439
00:29:01.320 --> 00:29:02.920
[Róża sighs]

440
00:29:03.000 --> 00:29:06.680
[sighs] My dear brother. I told you
to throw out those slippers.

441
00:29:06.760 --> 00:29:07.760
You're just jealous.

442
00:29:07.840 --> 00:29:09.160
-[Róża] Mm.
-[kisses]

443
00:29:09.240 --> 00:29:10.880
-[chuckles]
-[Maks] Okay. Okay. Hold that.

444
00:29:10.960 --> 00:29:11.960
[Ludwik] Oh. thank you.

445
00:29:13.040 --> 00:29:14.960
-Take this.
-[Maks] All right. let me see.

446
00:29:15.040 --> 00:29:16.200
Yeah.

447
00:29:16.280 --> 00:29:18.040
[sighs]

448
00:29:18.120 --> 00:29:22.920
"Your heart will break before one of our
super sturdy Eros Ultras ever will.

449
00:29:23.000 --> 00:29:25.040
We guarantee it." [laughs]

450
00:29:25.120 --> 00:29:28.240
"Rubber products.
Ludwik Apostołowicz and company."

451
00:29:28.320 --> 00:29:29.840
It has to be written in bold.

452
00:29:29.920 --> 00:29:33.360
Although. [sighs]
I mean. 15 bucks a box...

453
00:29:35.040 --> 00:29:37.440
...for only three to a pack.
that's pricey.

454
00:29:40.960 --> 00:29:42.960
Give me a discount
and I'll give you one. too.

455
00:29:43.040 --> 00:29:44.760
-[laughs]
-[Róża] For God's sakes. boys.

456
00:29:44.840 --> 00:29:47.120
-there's women in the room.
-[Maks laughing]

457
00:29:47.200 --> 00:29:48.520
[Ewa] You know. Mom.

458
00:29:48.600 --> 00:29:51.360
any taxi driver will sell you one
for just one zloty.

459
00:29:52.040 --> 00:29:52.960
Ewa.

460
00:29:54.200 --> 00:29:57.920
They buy them from the clerks
and resell them to passengers.

461
00:29:58.000 --> 00:30:01.160
Hmm. And cigarette packs.
so no one notices.

462
00:30:01.240 --> 00:30:03.400
-[Róża] Jesus Christ.
-Just a zloty?

463
00:30:03.480 --> 00:30:05.560
-Mm-hmm.
-How would a young lady know

464
00:30:05.640 --> 00:30:07.000
what those drivers do?

465
00:30:07.080 --> 00:30:09.000
-Well--
-Why don't you bring your aunt

466
00:30:09.080 --> 00:30:10.200
a cup. sweetheart?

467
00:30:10.280 --> 00:30:13.560
Looks like the help is slacking. [laughs]

468
00:30:15.480 --> 00:30:17.200
How do you feel this morning?

469
00:30:18.520 --> 00:30:19.760
My sister told me.

470
00:30:19.840 --> 00:30:21.560
Uh. I'm glad.

471
00:30:22.400 --> 00:30:23.880
-Oh. yeah?
-[Maks] Yes.

472
00:30:23.960 --> 00:30:25.160
Glad about what?

473
00:30:25.240 --> 00:30:27.320
Voronoff will help you have your baby.

474
00:30:27.400 --> 00:30:30.200
He's at the top of his field.
you're in good hands with him.

475
00:30:30.280 --> 00:30:34.000
Well. I won't be needing this anymore.
[chuckles softly]

476
00:30:34.080 --> 00:30:36.320
[footsteps receding]

477
00:30:38.160 --> 00:30:39.800
[Róża chuckles]

478
00:30:42.400 --> 00:30:43.800
Excuse me.

479
00:30:46.160 --> 00:30:47.400
Helena. hold on.

480
00:30:48.960 --> 00:30:50.240
Where are you going?

481
00:30:51.160 --> 00:30:53.240
That must have been some strong opium.

482
00:30:53.320 --> 00:30:56.120
Because I don't remember agreeing
to having a dead woman's ovary

483
00:30:56.200 --> 00:30:57.720
put inside of me.

484
00:30:57.800 --> 00:31:00.000
Professor Voronoff and Doctor Łabęda--

485
00:31:00.080 --> 00:31:03.120
Are gonna charge an arm and a leg.
I won't put my body through it.

486
00:31:03.200 --> 00:31:04.720
And what's your backup?

487
00:31:04.800 --> 00:31:07.280
-You won't be a goddess forever.
-[sighs]

488
00:31:07.360 --> 00:31:08.480
Maks is in his prime.

489
00:31:08.560 --> 00:31:10.600
Eventually. he'll find
someone younger than you.

490
00:31:10.680 --> 00:31:12.560
[laughs] You're a hypocrite.
you know that?

491
00:31:12.640 --> 00:31:13.720
I'm a woman. too.

492
00:31:13.800 --> 00:31:16.760
For us. it's better to die
than stop being alive.

493
00:31:19.240 --> 00:31:20.120
Auntie.

494
00:31:21.080 --> 00:31:24.480
Ludwik's told me to go to the office
and collect my things.

495
00:31:24.560 --> 00:31:27.760
[Róża] I approve. Work gives you wrinkles.

496
00:31:27.840 --> 00:31:29.000
Auntie.

497
00:31:33.760 --> 00:31:36.000
Did you hear about the Heckmann girl?

498
00:31:36.080 --> 00:31:36.920
Who?

499
00:31:37.000 --> 00:31:39.120
You know? The letter. "Pure-hearted Jan"?

500
00:31:39.200 --> 00:31:40.400
Well. she's dead.

501
00:31:43.480 --> 00:31:44.600
Uh...

502
00:31:45.400 --> 00:31:47.200
How do you know that?

503
00:31:47.280 --> 00:31:49.760
[Ewa] I read it in today's paper.

504
00:31:49.840 --> 00:31:53.800
She was a fallen woman.
died from an illegal abortion.

505
00:31:56.440 --> 00:31:58.800
-[door opens]
-[footsteps approaching]

506
00:32:00.680 --> 00:32:02.960
Time to go home. Mr. Heckmann.

507
00:32:03.040 --> 00:32:04.880
The doctor hates sleepyheads.

508
00:32:04.960 --> 00:32:06.920
Why didn't you wake me before?

509
00:32:07.000 --> 00:32:08.080
Was I supposed to?

510
00:32:08.160 --> 00:32:09.480
I was expecting a patient.

511
00:32:09.560 --> 00:32:11.440
Katarzyna Gawron. Pregnant.

512
00:32:11.520 --> 00:32:14.400
I was up all night.
I'm telling you. no one came.

513
00:32:16.000 --> 00:32:19.480
-[footsteps receding]
-[door opens. shuts]

514
00:32:19.560 --> 00:32:21.280
[Konieczny]
Katarzyna Gawron. 29 years old.

515
00:32:21.360 --> 00:32:23.440
[Janeczek] Another back alley abortion?

516
00:32:23.520 --> 00:32:27.840
Every year. I autopsy 200 women
who underwent abortions

517
00:32:27.920 --> 00:32:30.960
and died from acute blood infection.

518
00:32:31.040 --> 00:32:34.240
And that's just a fraction
of them. Superintendent.

519
00:32:36.920 --> 00:32:39.280
[slow. mysterious music playing]

520
00:32:57.480 --> 00:33:00.040
Here it is. Zuzanna Heckmann.

521
00:33:00.120 --> 00:33:01.520
[phone ringing]

522
00:33:04.720 --> 00:33:06.080
[phone continues ringing]

523
00:33:13.400 --> 00:33:14.760
[man speaking indistinctly]

524
00:33:22.120 --> 00:33:23.400
"A young artist seeks love

525
00:33:23.480 --> 00:33:26.720
and will fulfill the dreams
of a middle-aged man.

526
00:33:26.800 --> 00:33:28.920
Someone cultured. intelligent. and kind.

527
00:33:29.000 --> 00:33:33.440
{\an8}She seeks a kindred spirit. someone
she can share the rest of her life with.

528
00:33:33.520 --> 00:33:34.960
{\an8}Courageous."

529
00:33:35.040 --> 00:33:36.760
{\an8}Signed: "Courageous"

530
00:33:49.120 --> 00:33:50.640
What's this about?

531
00:33:53.080 --> 00:33:54.600
Sorry. ma'am. Uh...

532
00:33:54.680 --> 00:33:57.560
I'm looking for Mrs. Wróblewska.

533
00:33:57.640 --> 00:33:59.560
Editor Wróblewska.

534
00:33:59.640 --> 00:34:01.080
You found her.

535
00:34:01.160 --> 00:34:03.440
-To post an ad. you need to--
-No. I'm here for work.

536
00:34:03.520 --> 00:34:08.240
Though. if you can find me one.
I wouldn't mind a rich husband. [laughs]

537
00:34:10.880 --> 00:34:12.440
Hanka Stalówna.

538
00:34:16.320 --> 00:34:17.960
Helena Wróblewska.

539
00:34:19.400 --> 00:34:20.560
[chuckles]

540
00:34:20.640 --> 00:34:21.640
I'm sorry. but...

541
00:34:22.640 --> 00:34:25.360
who hired you and in what capacity?

542
00:34:25.440 --> 00:34:27.440
-Maks Wróblewski.
-[laughs]

543
00:34:27.520 --> 00:34:29.760
[Hanka] As the new assistant.

544
00:34:29.840 --> 00:34:31.040
[Helena] Mm-hmm.

545
00:35:13.880 --> 00:35:15.400
Hey. what is this?

546
00:35:15.480 --> 00:35:16.560
[music stops playing]

547
00:35:16.640 --> 00:35:18.040
Just playing a song. sir.

548
00:35:18.720 --> 00:35:19.920
Jarosy. what is this?

549
00:35:21.440 --> 00:35:23.800
[sighs] Uh...

550
00:35:23.880 --> 00:35:26.120
It was written by that man over there.

551
00:35:26.200 --> 00:35:27.840
Maksymilian Wróblewski.

552
00:35:27.920 --> 00:35:29.720
That's his name.

553
00:35:29.800 --> 00:35:31.960
How much do we pay him
to choose a different career?

554
00:35:32.040 --> 00:35:35.240
[laughs] He promised us free advertising.

555
00:35:35.320 --> 00:35:36.200
Uh... [sighs]

556
00:35:36.280 --> 00:35:38.720
In a marriage magazine. Uh. uh...

557
00:35:42.520 --> 00:35:45.000
Well. [clears throat]

558
00:35:49.240 --> 00:35:51.440
So. unfortunately...

559
00:35:51.520 --> 00:35:53.400
Unfortunately. Mr. Wróblewski.

560
00:35:53.480 --> 00:35:56.520
we can't include your waltz
in our new program.

561
00:35:57.800 --> 00:35:59.400
Uh... [stammering] B-b-b-but.

562
00:35:59.480 --> 00:36:03.160
but it's just that we already have
a piece very similar to it. [chuckles]

563
00:36:03.240 --> 00:36:07.520
Written by our very own literary director.
Mr. Julian Tuwim.

564
00:36:07.600 --> 00:36:08.800
Oh. really?

565
00:36:09.800 --> 00:36:13.040
I can't afford to be ruffling
Mr. Tuwin's feathers.

566
00:36:13.120 --> 00:36:16.320
He has pull
with all the critics in the city.

567
00:36:16.400 --> 00:36:17.640
Uh. they'd destroy us.

568
00:36:17.720 --> 00:36:19.760
Please relay this to Mr. Tuwim.

569
00:36:19.840 --> 00:36:22.360
-[Jarosy] Yes?
-That I...

570
00:36:23.560 --> 00:36:25.120
...have quite a bit of pull too.

571
00:36:25.200 --> 00:36:28.600
And I'm not afraid to use it.

572
00:36:28.680 --> 00:36:31.080
[slow instrumental music playing]

573
00:36:31.160 --> 00:36:32.040
Thank you.

574
00:36:35.480 --> 00:36:36.400
Ewa.

575
00:36:36.480 --> 00:36:38.080
[footsteps approaching]

576
00:36:38.760 --> 00:36:40.200
What are you doing here?

577
00:36:44.760 --> 00:36:47.720
I'm here because I... [sighs]

578
00:36:49.400 --> 00:36:51.040
...want you to have this.

579
00:36:54.840 --> 00:36:55.920
Ewa.

580
00:36:56.880 --> 00:36:59.280
I can't accept it. I'm Jewish.

581
00:36:59.360 --> 00:37:00.400
Keep it.

582
00:37:00.480 --> 00:37:02.520
Please take it.

583
00:37:02.600 --> 00:37:04.640
It was a present.

584
00:37:04.720 --> 00:37:08.960
My mom got it to protect me.
and now it'll protect you.

585
00:37:09.040 --> 00:37:11.120
I hope you're happy with your decision.

586
00:37:12.800 --> 00:37:15.880
I just need to convince my husband
to let me come back here.

587
00:37:15.960 --> 00:37:17.840
I wouldn't let you convince me.

588
00:37:20.640 --> 00:37:22.520
Marriage is just a formality.

589
00:37:23.480 --> 00:37:25.320
Everyone does it. it'll be all right.

590
00:37:27.680 --> 00:37:28.760
Ewa.

591
00:37:29.920 --> 00:37:32.440
I believe in one true love.

592
00:37:32.520 --> 00:37:34.160
In marriage.

593
00:37:34.240 --> 00:37:35.960
I want a family with you.

594
00:37:36.800 --> 00:37:39.800
I don't want to have to share you
with someone else.

595
00:38:03.000 --> 00:38:04.320
Don't leave me. Bruno.

596
00:38:06.960 --> 00:38:08.200
I'm sorry.

597
00:38:09.360 --> 00:38:10.800
[kissing]

598
00:38:15.600 --> 00:38:17.840
[piano music playing]

599
00:38:17.920 --> 00:38:19.680
[breathing heavily]

600
00:38:21.200 --> 00:38:22.400
[stomps]

601
00:38:22.920 --> 00:38:24.160
[stomping]

602
00:38:24.240 --> 00:38:26.440
[piano music continues playing]

603
00:38:32.080 --> 00:38:34.360
[footsteps approaching]

604
00:38:51.960 --> 00:38:54.640
[Maks] I wouldn't drink too much. darling.

605
00:38:54.720 --> 00:38:57.040
-We're going out.
-[sighs]

606
00:38:57.960 --> 00:39:00.000
Some files have gone missing
from the archive.

607
00:39:00.080 --> 00:39:03.280
We got two invitations
to the grand opening.

608
00:39:03.360 --> 00:39:04.600
Go get ready.

609
00:39:04.680 --> 00:39:08.000
-What opening?
-[Maks] A clinic or something.

610
00:39:08.080 --> 00:39:11.840
I don't really know.
What matters is Boy will be there.

611
00:39:11.920 --> 00:39:16.520
I'll run his article. and...
he'll handle Tuwim for me.

612
00:39:16.600 --> 00:39:18.600
Maks. the Heckmann girl is dead.

613
00:39:18.680 --> 00:39:22.800
-[unpleasant chords play abruptly]
-The one who ran an ad in our magazine.

614
00:39:22.880 --> 00:39:25.880
Someone went through and
destroyed her and her attacker's files.

615
00:39:25.960 --> 00:39:27.120
We're mixed up in a crime.

616
00:39:27.200 --> 00:39:29.160
We run ads. simple as that.

617
00:39:29.240 --> 00:39:30.320
They pay and we run them.

618
00:39:30.400 --> 00:39:31.640
Did you remove her ad?

619
00:39:31.720 --> 00:39:33.160
[Maks] Why does it matter?

620
00:39:33.240 --> 00:39:35.200
Best not stick your nose
where it doesn't belong.

621
00:39:35.280 --> 00:39:36.720
[Helena] We're shielding him.

622
00:39:36.800 --> 00:39:39.520
It's discretion. my dear.
It's what we do best.

623
00:39:42.560 --> 00:39:44.640
And if there's another victim?

624
00:39:47.640 --> 00:39:50.760
If you're that upset.
you could always quit.

625
00:39:53.960 --> 00:39:55.120
Go get ready.

626
00:39:58.040 --> 00:40:00.120
[slow instrumental music playing]

627
00:40:16.080 --> 00:40:18.400
[Tadeusz] Ladies and the few gentlemen.

628
00:40:18.480 --> 00:40:19.680
-Excuse me.
-Hello.

629
00:40:19.760 --> 00:40:23.200
In Warsaw alone. an estimated
20.000 miscarriages

630
00:40:23.280 --> 00:40:25.840
occur each and every year.

631
00:40:25.920 --> 00:40:28.120
-Nationwide. it may be 200.000.
-Hey. Good to see you.

632
00:40:28.200 --> 00:40:31.280
And that's a conservative estimate.
It's likely to be more.

633
00:40:31.360 --> 00:40:33.440
-[woman] Mrs. Wróblewska.
-[Helena] .

634
00:40:33.520 --> 00:40:35.680
[Tadeusz] Doctors estimate
that as many as half

635
00:40:35.760 --> 00:40:37.600
end in the women's death.

636
00:40:37.680 --> 00:40:41.600
The Conscious Motherhood Clinic
is meant to make women

637
00:40:41.680 --> 00:40:46.480
more aware of all the options
to prevent unwanted pregnancy.

638
00:40:46.560 --> 00:40:48.720
Because some are better off prevented.

639
00:40:48.800 --> 00:40:51.400
This is the beginning
of an awareness campaign

640
00:40:51.480 --> 00:40:53.280
to decrease preventable deaths.

641
00:40:53.360 --> 00:40:54.880
-Bravo. Boy!
-[man 2] Yes!

642
00:40:54.960 --> 00:40:56.720
-[man 3] Bravo!
-[crowd applauding]

643
00:40:56.800 --> 00:40:58.200
[man 4] Hear. hear. hear.

644
00:41:01.160 --> 00:41:04.000
[Tadeusz] In this effort.
we are helped by remarkable people

645
00:41:04.080 --> 00:41:07.040
like Dr. Justyna Budzińska-Tylicka.

646
00:41:07.120 --> 00:41:08.240
-[man] Bravo.
-[crowd cheer]

647
00:41:08.320 --> 00:41:10.640
And Dr. Herman Rubinraut.

648
00:41:10.720 --> 00:41:11.800
Thank you.

649
00:41:11.880 --> 00:41:14.760
I'm also proud to present
our social activist

650
00:41:14.840 --> 00:41:16.800
-from the medical school.
-[man 5] Hear. hear.

651
00:41:16.880 --> 00:41:18.200
[Tadeusz] Miss Helena Wojnarska.

652
00:41:20.080 --> 00:41:22.560
And Mr. Emil Heckmann.

653
00:41:23.440 --> 00:41:24.400
[man coughs]

654
00:41:24.480 --> 00:41:27.800
[Tadeusz] Mr. Heckmann.
are you here with us?

655
00:41:27.880 --> 00:41:29.600
[indistinct chattering]

656
00:41:30.840 --> 00:41:32.000
Emil Heckmann.

657
00:41:32.080 --> 00:41:33.600
[crowd applauding]

658
00:41:38.560 --> 00:41:40.520
Doctor. do you mind if I say a few words?

659
00:41:40.600 --> 00:41:41.600
You have the floor.

660
00:41:41.680 --> 00:41:43.600
[indistinct chatter]

661
00:41:44.640 --> 00:41:45.560
[Emil clears throat]

662
00:41:48.080 --> 00:41:49.680
Her name was Zuzanna.

663
00:41:53.160 --> 00:41:54.800
She was 17.

664
00:41:54.880 --> 00:41:56.560
[indistinct chatter stops]

665
00:41:56.640 --> 00:41:59.120
And she died after a botched abortion.

666
00:42:02.200 --> 00:42:04.680
-What's this about?
-[Emil] Where were we then?

667
00:42:06.720 --> 00:42:09.760
Where were you all when my sister
was bleeding to death?

668
00:42:09.840 --> 00:42:12.760
At some ceremony with more empty rhetoric?

669
00:42:12.840 --> 00:42:15.280
Sipping champagne.
saying meaningless slogans.

670
00:42:15.360 --> 00:42:18.200
telling each other how virtuous we are.

671
00:42:18.280 --> 00:42:22.480
We spout bullshit
about birth control and contraception.

672
00:42:23.040 --> 00:42:24.960
about fighting ignorance.

673
00:42:26.200 --> 00:42:30.400
What did any of us really do
to prevent what happened to Zuza?

674
00:42:32.360 --> 00:42:34.440
You all pat yourselves on the back...

675
00:42:36.320 --> 00:42:40.080
...for pitying the suffering of others.
How compassionate you are.

676
00:42:42.160 --> 00:42:44.360
Bravo. you should be proud.

677
00:42:45.600 --> 00:42:47.080
Especially you. Doctor.

678
00:42:48.240 --> 00:42:50.200
It's your specialty after all.

679
00:42:53.240 --> 00:42:54.760
[indistinct chatter]

680
00:42:56.080 --> 00:42:57.800
-Hold this.
-Helena!

681
00:42:57.880 --> 00:42:58.760
Helena!

682
00:42:58.840 --> 00:43:00.680
[man 6] I don't understand.

683
00:43:00.760 --> 00:43:03.000
This has never been talked about.

684
00:43:10.520 --> 00:43:11.880
[Helena] Mr. Heckmann.

685
00:43:12.360 --> 00:43:13.760
-Mr. Heckmann.
-[car door opens]

686
00:43:13.840 --> 00:43:15.480
I know what happened to your sister.

687
00:43:15.560 --> 00:43:17.400
-[car door shuts]
-[Konieczny] That's him!

688
00:43:17.480 --> 00:43:19.720
A man raped her. [panting]

689
00:43:19.800 --> 00:43:21.960
-Come with us. Mr. Heckmann.
-Who are you?

690
00:43:22.040 --> 00:43:23.480
-[Maks] Helena!
-What are you doing?

691
00:43:23.560 --> 00:43:24.520
Stop! Let go of him!

692
00:43:24.600 --> 00:43:26.520
-[Emil] I didn't do anything!
-[Helena] Stop!

693
00:43:26.600 --> 00:43:29.040
You're under arrest for aborting
your sister's pregnancy.

694
00:43:29.120 --> 00:43:31.520
-What are you doing? Stop it!
-[Emil] It wasn't me!

695
00:43:31.600 --> 00:43:33.440
[Emil grunting. groaning in pain]

696
00:43:33.520 --> 00:43:35.920
-Take him!
-[tense music playing]

697
00:43:36.000 --> 00:43:37.440
[camera shutter clicking]

698
00:43:37.520 --> 00:43:39.720
-[car door opens]
-[Emil] I didn't do it! [grunts]

699
00:43:39.800 --> 00:43:41.920
Find that bastard! I didn't do this!

700
00:43:42.000 --> 00:43:43.320
[camera shutter clicking]

701
00:43:43.400 --> 00:43:45.800
[indistinct chatter]

702
00:43:52.560 --> 00:43:54.440
[tense music continues playing]

703
00:44:07.600 --> 00:44:09.080
[tense music stops playing]

704
00:44:09.160 --> 00:44:11.080
[slow instrumental music playing]

705
00:47:17.720 --> 00:47:19.720
[slow instrumental music fades out]

706
00:47:20.305 --> 00:48:20.771
